=====================================================================
üìå SQL CHAR & VARCHAR (NOTES + EXAMPLES)
=====================================================================

CHAR and VARCHAR are **string (text) data types** used to store:
‚úî Names  
‚úî Codes  
‚úî Text values  

====================================================================
# 1Ô∏è‚É£ CHAR
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ CHAR
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
CHAR is a **fixed-length** string data type.

RULES:
‚úî Always uses full defined length  
‚úî Adds extra spaces if data is smaller  
‚úî Faster than VARCHAR  

BEST USED FOR:
‚úî Fixed size values  
‚úî Codes & flags  

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
create table person (
  gender char(1)
);

insert into person values ('M');
-- Stored as: 'M ' (1 char + space)

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 2Ô∏è‚É£ VARCHAR
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ VARCHAR
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
VARCHAR is a **variable-length** string data type.

RULES:
‚úî Uses only required space  
‚úî Saves memory  
‚úî Slightly slower than CHAR  

BEST USED FOR:
‚úî Names  
‚úî Emails  
‚úî Addresses  

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
create table user (
  name varchar(50)
);

insert into user values ('Akash');
-- Stored as: 'Akash' (no extra space)

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
COMPARISON TABLE
====================================================================

| Feature        | CHAR            | VARCHAR         |
|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Length        | Fixed           | Variable        |
| Space Usage   | More            | Efficient       |
| Speed         | Faster          | Slightly slower |
| Best For      | Codes, flags    | Text data       |

====================================================================
INTERVIEW ONE-LINERS
====================================================================

‚úî CHAR ‚Üí fixed length, fast  
‚úî VARCHAR ‚Üí flexible length, space-saving  
‚úî Use CHAR when length is constant  
‚úî Use VARCHAR when length varies  

====================================================================
SUMMARY
====================================================================

‚úî CHAR ‚Üí fixed size text  
‚úî VARCHAR ‚Üí dynamic size text  
‚úî CHAR wastes space if data is small  
‚úî VARCHAR stores only required size  

‚úî Common usage:
   ‚Ä¢ CHAR ‚Üí Gender, Country code  
   ‚Ä¢ VARCHAR ‚Üí Name, Email  

END OF NOTES
====================================================================
